<h3>New erasure codes for big data storage. </h3>
<p><a href="http://smahesh.com/HadoopUSC/">Xorbas HDFS</a> is a module for Hadoop Mapreduce that implements Locally repairable codes. These new codes can perform rebuilds with significantly smaller disk IO and network traffic compared to Reed-Solomon and other other classic codes. Our prototype is open source and available on Github and was tested on Amazon and Facebook clusters. It is a modification of the HDFS RAID module used by Facebook for big data storage protection. </p>
<p><a href="http://smahesh.com/HadoopUSC/">Project homepage</a> </p>
